<plot>'The Field at Sunset' gives an intimate perspective into the psychological turmoil of Leonard, an odd, socially inept man who lives in isolation, and how disarrayed his mind becomes when a neighbor woman unexpectedly takes an interest in his eccentric lifestyle. The dynamic relationship becomes both difficult and beautiful for both people in this portrait of human frustration and loneliness.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?557349</url></doc>
